  "prompt": "Has Jimmy Wales ever come to India?",
  "response": "Yes, Jimmy Wales, the co-founder of Wikipedia, has visited India on multiple occasions. His visits have often been related to promoting open knowledge, digital literacy, and the growth of Wikipedia in India. For example:\n\n1. **February 2011**: Wales visited India to promote Wikipedia and its importance as a free, open-source encyclopedia. He spoke at events in cities like Mumbai and New Delhi, emphasizing the need for more contributors from India to enrich content in Indian languages.\n\n2. **November 2011**: He returned to India to attend the **WikiConference India** in Mumbai, where he discussed the future of Wikipedia and its role in the digital age.\n\n3. **February 2016**: Wales visited India again to encourage more participation in Wikipedia, particularly in regional languages, during events in cities like Hyderabad.\n\nJimmy Wales has consistently highlighted the importance of India as a growing hub for internet users and contributors to the Wikimedia ecosystem. His visits have been instrumental in raising awareness and fostering collaboration within the Indian Wikipedia community.",
